Let's redo another memorable GAC event: Lac de Monteynard-Avignonet and its two Passerelles!

== üö£ Canoe: 11km hike to Bois Fran√ßais and back in Grenoble with 20km canoe üö£ ==
We will do 11km hikes to go to Bois Fran√ßais, have lunch there and then take canoe at 2:45pm and go back in Grenoble (at Pont d‚ÄôOxford near CEA)

Topo & GPX track: https://s.42l.fr/hbxWc5uW
‚ñ∂üí° Download GPX track on your phone.
Distance: 11km
Time: ~2/3h of hike + 1/2h lunch + 3/4h of canoe
D+: 70m

Meet at 9am at parking "Esplanade du Souvenir Fran√ßais" near Parc Paul Mistral:
- https://www.osm.org/way/69486256
- https://goo.gl/maps/BAbHQ153PcNgunPd6

== About canoeing ==
I've done exactly the same event 1 year ago. And in my opinion, it is open for beginners. There is no "extreme" difficulty. You will have to row your boat with another people. No need to have a lot of muscles, cause the river will push you gently until the end of the 20km.

‚ùó‚ùó It's MANDATORY to know how to swim. At least 25 meters with your head temporary under the water. See https://canoe-grenoble.com/infos-pratiques/ (READ IT)

Note that we won't have any shadow during the whole afternoon. So take sun-cream/sunglasses/water/etc. Wearing shoes and a long short will prevent you to get burned by the sun.

== üí≤ How to subscribe? üí≤ ==
1. Subscribe on this meetup event waiting list
2. Send me through meetup or WhatsApp:
- first name
- last name
- birth date
- zipcode
3. I will call the company to make a reservation with your name
4. When done, I will add you in the "Going list" in meetup
5. Bring 25‚Ç¨ cash (only) on Sunday

== üí° Rules üí° ==
- Don't be (too) late üòá We won't wait for you, especially if you don't send any message.
- Don't throw any dump in nature even egg shell, fruit pelt, ... üå≥ ‚ù§Ô∏è You
- You are responsible of your own security
- Covid rules: https://www.gouvernement.fr/en/coronavirus-covid-19

== ‚ùî What do you need ‚ùî ==
Don't bring a lot of stuff, cause we need them to fit in a tiny waterproof barrel.

- A tiny bag to carry all your stuffs, NOT A BIG BAG
- Water ready shoes ü•æ (any kind of shoes that you don't mind to put in the water)
- üßÉ Water + ü•ï food for lunch + üç´ Some snack

So you need to know how to swim to participate! If you have never done it in the past, no biggies ! There will be a professionnal guide with us all the time making sure that we stay alive. We can be maximum 9 people (3 cars to do the activities). For now I can bring 4 people (including me) with my car. So we need other cars. You can either sleep up-there or go back to Grenoble with the rest of the group. (I will sleep up there) üòäüå†
